8.40	United_Future_Organization	United Future Organization	United Future Organization otherwise known as UFO is a nu-jazz duo made up of Japanese-born Tadashi Yabe Yabe Tadashi) and Frenchman Raphael Sebbag ). In 1994, the group appeared on the Red Hot Organization's compilation album, Stolen Moments: Red Hot + Cool. The album, meant to raise awareness and funds in support of the AIDS epidemic in relation to the African American community, was heralded as "Album of the Year" by Time Magazine. One of the three original founding members,Toshio Matsuura Matsuura Toshio) left the group in 2002 to work with Universal Japan on a remix album project.	
